The paper deals with a communication problem involving caching, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of caches with limited memory, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The problem involves multiple users accessing a central server, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses index coding as a tool to derive bounds, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the trade-off between rate and memory, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC).
